The paper is about designing activation functions for deep neural networks, which is a topic closely related to neural network optimization and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves comparing the performance of different architectures on standard datasets, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the datasets used in the paper are related to computer vision (Fashion-MNIST, CIFAR-10, and ILSVRC-2012), suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible sub-category. The paper also involves tuning hyper-parameters, which is a common task in machine learning and falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks, such as sentiment analysis, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
